===Verb===
{{en-verb|++}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To regard (someone or something) as [[horrifying]] or [[detestable]]; to feel great [[repugnance]] toward. {{defdate|First attested from around (1350 to 1470).}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=4}}</ref>
#:{{syn|en|detest|disdain|loathe}}
#:{{ux|en|I absolutely '''abhor''' being stuck in traffic jams}}
#* {{RQ:KJV|Romans|12|9|text='''abhorre''' that which is euill, cleaue to that which is good.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|obsolete|impersonal}} To fill with horror or [[disgust]]. {{defdate|Attested from the mid 16<sup>th</sup> century until the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Othello|4|1|text=It does '''abhor''' me now I speak the word.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To turn aside or avoid; to keep away from; to reject.
# {{lb|en|transitive|canon law|obsolete}} To [[protest]] against; to reject [[solemnly]].
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 8|2|4|text=I utterly '''abhor''', yea, from my soul Refuse you for my judge.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|obsolete}} To feel horror, [[disgust]], or [[dislike]] (towards); to be [[contrary]] or [[averse]] (to); {{non-gloss definition|construed with ''from''}}. {{defdate|Attested from the mid 16<sup>th</sup> century until the mid 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{RQ:Elyot Governour|text=the daunce were to their honour and memorie, whiche moste of all '''abhored''' from Christes religion}}
#* {{RQ:Milton Divorce|book=II|chapter=7|text=Either then the law by harmless and needful dispenses, which the gospel is now made to deny, must have anticipated and exceeded the grace of the gospel, or else must be found to have given politic and superficial graces without real pardon, saying in general, “do this and live,” and yet deceiving and damning underhand with unsound and hollow permissions; which is utterly '''abhorring''' from the end of all law, as hath been shewed.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|obsolete}} Differ entirely from. {{defdate|Attested from the mid 16<sup>th</sup> century until the late 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>

